1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:07,080

2
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:49,450

3
00:00:49,450 --> 00:00:55,450

4
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:06,900
What is this? Is this the military?

5
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,240
Hey, why did we come here?

6
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,750
Sae Bom is here.

7
00:01:11,750 --> 00:01:16,520
Then you should have let me off earlier! I have to hand out rice cakes.

8
00:01:27,340 --> 00:01:29,270
Should we practice?

9
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:32,360
I will take that one.

10
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:42,580

11
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:57,260

12
00:02:10,850 --> 00:02:13,130

13
00:02:13,790 --> 00:02:15,560
Hurry!

14
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:20,450
No, don't open it!

15
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:41,180

16
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:02,950
Check that the other cars are locked.

17
00:03:03,620 --> 00:03:05,760
- I have to get Seung Young out. 
 - What?

18
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:08,440
He was fine just a minute ago.

19
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:24,930

20
00:03:29,790 --> 00:03:31,400
Seung Young!

21
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:33,360
Are you okay?

22
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:37,540
Hyun, how did you get here?

23
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:43,230
I'm glad I wasn't late.

24
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:58,320

25
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,850
Open your mouth.

26
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:16,920
I'm sorry. I don't know why I did it.

27
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:22,170
It was unfair to die like this so I guess I wanted to do something.

28
00:05:26,910 --> 00:05:29,400
Did something happen inside?

29
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:37,400
I went inside. And those people were...

30
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:41,490
all completely crazy.

31
00:05:42,690 --> 00:05:45,790
- I saw. 
 - Sae Bom,

32
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:49,720
what if I become like that?

33
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:54,040
My wife and my children.

34
00:06:04,460 --> 00:06:07,330
I'm disappointed in you, Lieutenant.

35
00:06:07,330 --> 00:06:09,600
Yoon Sae Bom.

36
00:06:12,670 --> 00:06:17,990
Five people have already been infected while trying to care for that person.

37
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,390
What are we supposed to do?

38
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:32,860
How did you know the flare would be effective?

39
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:35,750
Otherwise, there's no reason for the soldiers to carry it around.

40
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:39,630
It's not as if they're repressing massive terror, and there are already multiple people infected.

41
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:45,490
I found out when a few of the infected tried to escape the facility.

42
00:06:45,490 --> 00:06:48,930
So you just lock them up here and wait for them to die?

43
00:06:48,930 --> 00:06:54,000
What else should we do? They have no rationality, and the normal ones keep looking for fresh blood.

44
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,900
Should we give them a live offering?

45
00:06:55,900 --> 00:06:59,250
They're still living people, though. We have to endure it.

46
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:01,430
This is enduring it.

47
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:06,460
We protect those with mild cases and isolate the severe ones.

48
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:12,760
Listen here, Han Tae Seok. What if your family became like that?

49
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:16,680
Be honest. You see them as monsters.

50
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:19,240
You'll shoot at them without a second thought if they come at you.

51
00:07:24,980 --> 00:07:28,230
Do you know what we learned through COVID-19?

52
00:07:28,230 --> 00:07:31,630
What? That we should wash our hands well?

53
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:37,190
Eating and living are more important than a few people tearing each other apart.

54
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:41,930
I'm enduring with all my strength to protect my family.

55
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:55,370
How much longer will you work in the shadows like this?

56
00:07:55,370 --> 00:07:59,730
You have to announce it to the public and discuss what will happen to the infected.

57
00:07:59,730 --> 00:08:02,970
I will. The news media are already catching on.

58
00:08:02,970 --> 00:08:07,830
Hurry, or I'll break the news.

59
00:08:11,930 --> 00:08:15,180
Let's not see each other again, if we can help it.

60
00:08:15,180 --> 00:08:17,110
Oh, one more thing.

61
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:32,470
These people are also enduring with all their strength.

62
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:55,900

63
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:30,230

64
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:35,860
Finally, I can breathe now.

65
00:09:44,940 --> 00:09:50,700
I had an installment saving plan in dollars, and I even planned a trip. What a waste.

66
00:09:52,770 --> 00:09:54,800
Give me your hand.

67
00:10:00,030 --> 00:10:03,070
It has almost healed, though.

68
00:10:07,590 --> 00:10:09,890
This will sting.

69
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:19,590
Is it fine for me to be okay by myself?

70
00:10:19,590 --> 00:10:23,130
Hey, it's a relief you're okay, at least.

71
00:10:23,130 --> 00:10:26,000
There'll be treatments and vaccines soon.

72
00:10:28,290 --> 00:10:34,530
This thing will pass safely eventually

73
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:36,890
so don't worry.

74
00:10:38,490 --> 00:10:43,900
Can those people recover, too?

75
00:10:47,740 --> 00:10:50,060
I hope so.

76
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:07,550
Oh, hello.

77
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:13,500
Did you look into the T-shirts? Large size?

78
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:17,630
I was preoccupied today. I'll bring it next time.

79
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:41,210
Unni! Mom, it's the special forces Unni across from us.

80
00:11:41,210 --> 00:11:46,470
Oh, hello. I heard you took good care of Seo Yoon. Thank you.

81
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:05,820
That place earlier was nice, right?

82
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:15,990
Husband? He's handsome.

83
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:54,180

84
00:12:57,750 --> 00:13:02,570
Found it.

85
00:13:02,570 --> 00:13:04,480
Okay.

86
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,460
Are you okay?

87
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:23,290
Nothing. It's just weird to return to our everyday lives so easily.

88
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:25,960
Should we just do it another time?

89
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:29,120
No, we are trying to hold onto our normal life.

90
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,760
I can do it.

91
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:37,420
But do you think she'll believe we are getting married?

92
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:42,280
Of course, she'll think we love each other to death so don't worry.

93
00:13:44,340 --> 00:13:49,080
For now, chamomile. It'll warm you up.

94
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:51,850
- Do I look okay? 
 - Yes.

95
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:56,300
Look at me properly first.

96
00:13:57,680 --> 00:14:00,270
All right. Let's see.

97
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:08,930
You look fine. You look pretty.

98
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:12,690
But who would think we are getting married

99
00:14:12,690 --> 00:14:16,180
because of the apartment? Of course, she'll think it is because we love each other to death. You're so—

100
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:18,090
 Sae Bom!

101
00:14:19,310 --> 00:14:20,570
Hello, Mother.

102
00:14:20,570 --> 00:14:23,780
 From the moment I first saw you two, I knew it would work out well.

103
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:28,620
When I saw you two sitting together in the ambulance at the school, you looked so good together.

104
00:14:28,620 --> 00:14:32,050
Oh, that photo is from back then!

105
00:14:32,050 --> 00:14:34,830
 We are trying not to forget our initial resolution.

106
00:14:34,830 --> 00:14:38,740
Sae Bom, I have something I wanted to say to you.

107
00:14:38,740 --> 00:14:40,500
Yes, please go ahead.

108
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:44,120
 Son, can you go elsewhere for a minute? I have something to say to Sae Bom.

109
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:47,890
Just tell me later, and I'll tell her for you.

110
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:52,320
 Oh? Do you have noise issues with the neighbor?

111
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:54,590
 That can be a headache.

112
00:14:54,590 --> 00:14:57,350
Go tell them to be quiet.

113
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,730
Go ahead, Mother.

114
00:15:04,730 --> 00:15:08,260
 Sae Bom, thank you so much.

115
00:15:08,260 --> 00:15:11,370
 Thanks to you, Hyun seems to be living a normal life.

116
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:16,600
Mother, Hyun does quite well without me.

117
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:20,920
 He's a good boy, but sometimes he just can't control his rage.

118
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:25,170
 After he couldn't play baseball anymore, he started hanging out with bad guys.

119
00:15:25,170 --> 00:15:30,030
 I had prepared to send him to study in America, but he said he couldn't speak English so he wouldn't do it.

120
00:15:30,030 --> 00:15:34,430
I think detective work suits him. Catching bad guys and all that.

121
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:49,920
- It's late at night. I was wondering what was going on. 
 - I'm sorry.

122
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:54,750
I'm not here to hear an apology. I'm really worried. It's nothing serious, right?

123
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:56,830
I, well...

124
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:02,320
Hello. I live below, and it is a bit noisy.

125
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:04,450
I apologize.

126
00:16:05,870 --> 00:16:07,550
Wait...

127
00:16:09,790 --> 00:16:14,520
I couldn't tell you yesterday, but my wife is ill.

128
00:16:14,520 --> 00:16:18,620
She keeps throwing things and screaming.

129
00:16:18,620 --> 00:16:20,390
So this is...?

130
00:16:20,390 --> 00:16:23,030
She's from my wife's dermatology clinic...

131
00:16:23,030 --> 00:16:28,050
She's the chief dermatologist there. She's here to help since she's worried.

132
00:16:32,330 --> 00:16:35,890
She took sleeping pills and laid down so she'll be all right.

133
00:16:35,890 --> 00:16:37,890
Does she bite or try to scratch you at all?

134
00:16:37,890 --> 00:16:42,760
It's not like that. She's just sensitive.

135
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:46,670
It won't happen again. My apologies.

136
00:16:49,790 --> 00:16:51,530
What is it?

137
00:16:56,810 --> 00:17:02,260
What is the name of the dermatology clinic?

138
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:08,100
I think we should have a wedding. Who could officiate it?

139
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:13,160
Hyung Jung Gook?

140
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:18,190
That sounds reasonable, but does he speak well in public?

141
00:17:19,370 --> 00:17:20,810
No.

142
00:17:21,570 --> 00:17:26,630
We can just go out by ourselves and speak for ourselves. Saying we will live happily together.

143
00:17:26,630 --> 00:17:28,860
That sounds good, too.

144
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:35,690
Seung Young is good at singing. I hope he can recover before then.

145
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:40,050
Should we go on a honeymoon too? Where should we go?

146
00:17:40,050 --> 00:17:42,860
Somewhere you always wanted to go to?

147
00:17:42,860 --> 00:17:46,100
What if I said I wanted to tour buffets?

148
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:48,820
I can't leave one place until I have ten plates.

149
00:17:48,820 --> 00:17:51,600
Excuse me, I used to be a baseball player.

150
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:54,170
I eat a scary amount.

151
00:17:55,980 --> 00:18:00,030
Thinking about eating makes me hungry. Quick, let's sleep.

152
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:03,860
All right. Good night.

153
00:18:03,860 --> 00:18:05,590
You, too.

154
00:18:52,890 --> 00:18:58,460
 The number of patients suffering from the disease that makes them bite others and drink blood is increasing,

155
00:18:58,460 --> 00:19:02,510
 but the government still insists that they are not clear on the classification of the illness.

156
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:05,040
 - They are cautious to make announcements.  
 - Honey.

157
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:07,270
Honey!

158
00:19:07,270 --> 00:19:09,590
We don't have that kind of money!

159
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:13,260
So are we just going to live like this? What if she collapses?

160
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:15,930
Why do you say such negative things?

161
00:19:15,930 --> 00:19:19,570
Nothing happened so far. We just have to continue taking good care of her.

162
00:19:19,570 --> 00:19:23,320
We're already being discriminated against for living on lease. What if it gets out she's sick?

163
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:25,230
I'll go visit Unni from across the hall.

164
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:27,870
We can just say that it's a study abroad and leave without anyone knowing.

165
00:19:27,870 --> 00:19:31,080
No one will find out. Honey.

166
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:34,690
 Where am I supposed to get that kind of money?

167
00:19:46,570 --> 00:19:51,550
Unni, it's me, Seo Yoon.

168
00:19:51,550 --> 00:19:54,100
Hi! I have some leftover rice cakes. Do you want some?

169
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:56,270
Can I?

170
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:04,070
Even love has its moments of crisis.

171
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:07,430
It looks like it was a pretty severe crisis.

172
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:08,810
Where is Ahjussi?

173
00:20:08,810 --> 00:20:12,190
He's working. He said he had orders from above.

174
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:15,140

175
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:17,260
 - Hello?  
 - Hello.

176
00:20:17,260 --> 00:20:19,630
Is the head dermatologist, Park Min Ji, there?

177
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:25,630
 Oh, yes. She's on leave for a week. We can only take reservations from next week.

178
00:20:25,630 --> 00:20:29,030
Then is the chief dermatologist also on leave?

179
00:20:29,030 --> 00:20:32,040
 The chief dermatologist? Which one do you mean?

180
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:35,630
She had hair that came to her waist, and she had double eyelids.

181
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:38,030
 Oh, Woo Sang Hee. She's on a monthly leave.

182
00:20:38,030 --> 00:20:41,060
 Oh, she's right there. One second.

183
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:49,300
What's this? Are you looking to get your skin taken care of?

184
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,690
I'm just bothered by the neighbor upstairs.

185
00:20:52,690 --> 00:20:54,570
Oh, noisy neighbors.

186
00:20:54,570 --> 00:20:57,150
That will really drive you crazy.

187
00:20:58,750 --> 00:21:03,400
Hey. By the way, we are to halt the investigation on the car wash center.

188
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:07,190
Chief said another team was taking care of it so we should stay out of it.

189
00:21:07,190 --> 00:21:09,130
Han Tae Seok?

190
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:15,330
Is it really okay? Isn't it a dangerous disease?

191
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:27,910

192
00:21:30,860 --> 00:21:32,140
Hey, Mom. What is it?

193
00:21:32,140 --> 00:21:33,490
 Are you okay?

194
00:21:33,490 --> 00:21:35,660
I heard you got tested for the Madman Rabies.

195
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:37,690
They said it's okay. It's nothing.

196
00:21:37,690 --> 00:21:40,380
I still need to self-isolate for a while.

197
00:21:40,380 --> 00:21:44,980
Turn on the television right now. It's a mess.

198
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:55,610
 Is anyone there?

199
00:22:01,100 --> 00:22:03,030
 They're not human.

200
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:05,240
 Their hands...

201
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:10,050
 The video you just watched was obtained exclusively by us.

202
00:22:10,050 --> 00:22:11,820
 Let me say this again.

203
00:22:11,820 --> 00:22:14,470
 Our network obtained the footage exclusively.

204
00:22:14,470 --> 00:22:18,480
 An anonymous tipper snuck into a secret government facility

205
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:22,260
 and sent this to us after filming on his phone.

206
00:22:22,260 --> 00:22:24,320
- Are you watching the news? 
  - They never even acknowledged this existence,

207
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:26,960
 and this disease has only been a rumor thus far.

208
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:28,410
 They bite people

209
00:22:28,410 --> 00:22:30,250
 and drink their blood.

210
00:22:30,250 --> 00:22:32,820
 Madman Rabies does exist.

211
00:22:32,820 --> 00:22:34,450
 Perhaps the government is keeping this secret...

212
00:22:34,450 --> 00:22:35,750
I'll call you back.

213
00:22:35,750 --> 00:22:38,300
 This is the only exsting proof so far.

214
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:43,460
 The informant of this video could not be contacted after the release of this video.

215
00:22:43,460 --> 00:22:47,320
 Our reporters are working to find out what happened to the informant.

216
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:50,330
 They are doing their best.

217
00:22:58,570 --> 00:23:00,540
What is this?

218
00:23:00,540 --> 00:23:04,160
The stores just opened up, but it looks like we are being banned from gathering again.

219
00:23:06,610 --> 00:23:08,620
I want to bite everyone.

220
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:10,810
- Send me to the hospital. 
 - You just said it was COVID-19.

221
00:23:10,810 --> 00:23:13,190
It's Madman Rabies!

222
00:23:25,620 --> 00:23:28,310
Don't say something so dangerous.

223
00:23:28,310 --> 00:23:30,990
Go easy on him.

224
00:23:30,990 --> 00:23:32,790
Are you okay?

225
00:23:33,890 --> 00:23:35,790
Where are you going?

226
00:23:35,790 --> 00:23:37,380
Where are you going? You have to get tested.

227
00:23:37,380 --> 00:23:39,860
The hospital.

228
00:23:39,860 --> 00:23:42,940
You'll lose your place in the line.

229
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:46,990
Are you going camping?

230
00:23:47,830 --> 00:23:51,160
We just got the emergency alert text, but there aren't a lot of people.

231
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:54,910
The emergency alert text comes every day. How can we react to it all the time?

232
00:23:54,910 --> 00:23:58,390
Not unless some people die and the number of infected rises to the thousands.

233
00:23:58,390 --> 00:24:00,810
Would you like these delivered?

234
00:24:00,810 --> 00:24:03,940
- Just the water and rice,  please. 
 - Okay.

235
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:14,820

236
00:24:14,820 --> 00:24:18,460
This is me. What is this about?

237
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:23,590
I'm the apartment representative. Suite 1202.

238
00:24:24,820 --> 00:24:27,350
I blurred your face for your privacy.

239
00:24:27,350 --> 00:24:30,210
I ask that you be more careful from now on.

240
00:24:30,310 --> 00:24:34,030
What if you block the door and there is a fire?

241
00:24:34,030 --> 00:24:38,360
The name of that door is "firewall." It is to prevent fires.

242
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:40,360
It keeps the fire from spreading,

243
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:43,830
but what would happen if it was kept open?

244
00:24:43,830 --> 00:24:45,330
The fire would spread, wouldn't it?

245
00:24:45,330 --> 00:24:47,930
It should be closed, but not blocked.

246
00:24:47,930 --> 00:24:49,400
If it's blocked, no one could even escape.

247
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:52,610
It was the decision of the building's firefighting administrator.

248
00:24:52,610 --> 00:24:56,600
Excuse me, Firefighting Administrator would mean an outsourcing agency.

249
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:59,450
Is that the official statement from them?

250
00:24:59,450 --> 00:25:00,490
Who are you?

251
00:25:00,490 --> 00:25:03,470
I live in suite 401.

252
00:25:04,550 --> 00:25:06,860
On lease...

253
00:25:10,010 --> 00:25:12,500
Do you know the doctor from suite 601?

254
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:15,780
She's suffering from people who constantly knock on her door.

255
00:25:15,780 --> 00:25:18,930
According to her husband, she canceled the appointments at her clinic,

256
00:25:18,930 --> 00:25:20,650
and she's sick in bed.

257
00:25:20,650 --> 00:25:22,630
Is that what they said?

258
00:25:22,630 --> 00:25:24,440
After making all that noise that night?

259
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:27,820
Ms., noises from neighbors have no set direction.

260
