00:52:24,470 --> 00:52:26,300
Well...

521
00:52:31,050 --> 00:52:33,510
Geez...

522
00:52:42,080 --> 00:52:45,310
I decided to get the surgery.

523
00:52:46,140 --> 00:52:48,020
Did you decide?

524
00:52:48,020 --> 00:52:53,980
My mom is extremely worried, but it's also worrisome if the disease is spread in the apartment.

525
00:52:53,980 --> 00:52:57,270
My wounds don't heal well.

526
00:52:57,270 --> 00:53:00,150
I take antibiotics too.

527
00:53:00,150 --> 00:53:04,470
I asked to leave quietly while all this was going on and get the surgery.

528
00:53:04,470 --> 00:53:05,930
When do you leave?

529
00:53:05,930 --> 00:53:09,810
I will go for an exam when my mom comes home later.

530
00:53:11,830 --> 00:53:14,350
It's that ahjussi who was on TV.

531
00:53:15,460 --> 00:53:17,510
Is he your friend, Unni?

532
00:53:17,510 --> 00:53:21,000
No. I just know him.

533
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:22,520
What brings you here?

534
00:53:22,520 --> 00:53:27,000
Madman Rabies is spreading throughout the apartment building.

535
00:53:31,550 --> 00:53:34,350
One person already caught it.

536
00:53:34,350 --> 00:53:36,450
Are there more infected people?

537
00:53:36,450 --> 00:53:42,140
I questioned a drug dealer, and he says he sold the drug at the underground gym.

538
00:53:42,140 --> 00:53:46,130
He sold them saying it helps you focus and for dieting.

539
00:53:46,130 --> 00:53:51,090
Park Min Ji from the sixth floor was one of the buyers.

540
00:53:51,090 --> 00:53:54,060
 - Hello, Ma'am. 
 - Hello.

541
00:54:15,810 --> 00:54:17,410
 Hello.

542
00:54:17,410 --> 00:54:19,170
 Aigoo, Ma'am. You're here.

543
00:54:19,170 --> 00:54:21,950
 - How have you been? 
 - Good.

544
00:54:21,950 --> 00:54:23,610
 - Thanks. 
 - Thank you.

545
00:54:23,610 --> 00:54:26,080
 Thank you. Enjoy your workout.

546
00:54:27,040 --> 00:54:29,150

547
00:54:29,150 --> 00:54:33,330
There must be quite a few people like Park Min Ji inside the apartment.

548
00:54:33,330 --> 00:54:38,490
I'm sure some people are living quietly, hiding the signs of their illness.

549
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:43,370
The numbers of infected will increase quietly like that and explode all at once.

550
00:54:43,370 --> 00:54:47,560
What are you doing here then? You should start the investigation.

551
00:54:47,560 --> 00:54:51,470
Will that solve the issue? When we don't have any treatment or vaccine?

552
00:54:51,470 --> 00:54:56,520
We don't know when the apartment residents will start having symptoms. Where should we keep them and monitor them?

553
00:54:56,520 --> 00:55:00,860
It's not like we can slaughter all of them like the swine flu.

554
00:55:00,860 --> 00:55:03,390
What will you do then?

555
00:55:03,390 --> 00:55:06,710
Do you have another way?

556
00:55:06,710 --> 00:55:11,350
I do have another way.

557
00:55:27,920 --> 00:55:31,740

558
00:55:51,990 --> 00:55:54,830
 What is happening?

559
00:55:54,830 --> 00:55:57,540
 Why are you trapping us in?

560
00:55:57,540 --> 00:55:59,470
 What is this for?

561
00:56:03,450 --> 00:56:05,240
 Come on!

562
00:56:24,010 --> 00:56:27,160
As luck would have it, only residents are allowed to use the gym.

563
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:29,220
And half of the residents are families,

564
00:56:29,220 --> 00:56:33,610
and the daycare inside the apartment hasn't opened yet.

565
00:56:35,280 --> 00:56:37,350
Will you block off the entire apartment building?

566
00:56:37,350 --> 00:56:42,310
Until we obtain the workforce and location to monitor all the infected.

567
00:56:42,310 --> 00:56:47,730
You should notify the apartment's residents so people can mentally prepare.

568
00:56:47,730 --> 00:56:53,260
They won't mentally prepare but run away and spread the disease.

569
00:56:54,480 --> 00:56:56,190
You can get out, Yoon Sae Bom.

570
00:56:56,190 --> 00:57:01,040
When it comes to work of this nature, we are always in need of decisive people.

571
00:57:07,490 --> 00:57:09,680
It's my fault.

572
00:57:11,170 --> 00:57:18,440
When I found out what you were doing at the dorm, I should've released everything to the newspapers, news, everywhere.

573
00:57:18,440 --> 00:57:20,330
That wouldn't have changed anything.

574
00:57:20,330 --> 00:57:25,050
You have to prioritize things when it comes to dealing with these situations.

575
00:57:25,050 --> 00:57:30,230
Who is a more essential person and what is more needed...

576
00:57:30,230 --> 00:57:33,050
I guess I'm an essential person.

577
00:57:42,290 --> 00:57:47,410
However, I decided to live here, and this is my home.

578
00:57:48,150 --> 00:57:50,450
Whether it's noise problems or Madman Rabies,

579
00:57:50,450 --> 00:57:55,260
running away isn't my style.

580
00:57:56,350 --> 00:57:58,300
Good day.

581
00:58:09,450 --> 00:58:12,640
Hey, I'm in front of your house.

582
00:58:13,710 --> 00:58:16,820
Hey, I came all the way here. How can I go back?

583
00:58:16,820 --> 00:58:18,550
Yes.

584
00:58:20,520 --> 00:58:22,300
What the heck?

585
00:58:32,750 --> 00:58:37,230
This is my apartment building. Is something wrong?

586
00:58:37,230 --> 00:58:38,840
If you go inside now, you can't get out again.

587
00:58:38,840 --> 00:58:42,950
What? What is he talking about?

588
00:58:42,950 --> 00:58:44,970
Yes. What floor are you on?

589
00:58:44,970 --> 00:58:46,940
I'm coming in right now.

590
00:59:06,390 --> 00:59:09,950
Hyun, I'm trapped inside.

591
00:59:09,950 --> 00:59:12,550
Don't get into a fight trying to come in.

592
00:59:12,550 --> 00:59:15,760
If my mom calls you, tell her I'm okay.

593
00:59:15,760 --> 00:59:19,910
 What are you talking about? Where are you trapped?

594
00:59:19,910 --> 00:59:23,560
I'll protect the apartment.

595
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:27,470
Wait, Bom, tell me exactly what's going on. What's...

596
00:59:31,650 --> 00:59:35,440
I mean, I was going to tell you when I knew for sure...

597
00:59:44,660 --> 00:59:47,440
I thought I was in here alone.

598
00:59:54,850 --> 00:59:58,980
Sae Bom, I have to catch him right now.

599
00:59:58,980 --> 01:00:02,680
It's okay. No one can get out.

600
01:00:35,990 --> 01:00:41,880

601
01:00:41,880 --> 01:00:48,860

602
01:00:57,650 --> 01:00:59,620
 ~ Preview ~ 
 Let me leave.

603
01:00:59,620 --> 01:01:01,870
 You two could likely be infectious.

604
01:01:01,870 --> 01:01:05,090
 You don't know how things have changed on the outside.

605
01:01:05,090 --> 01:01:07,710
 Did you take that drug, too?

606
01:01:07,710 --> 01:01:09,470
 You know who took them, right?

607
01:01:09,470 --> 01:01:12,960
 No one knows how drastically people would change when push comes to shove.

608
01:01:12,960 --> 01:01:14,410
 What are you doing right now?

609
01:01:14,410 --> 01:01:18,350
 They say we can't leave now. Other apartment buildings voted and decided that.

610
01:01:18,350 --> 01:01:20,510
 Yoon Sae Bom, are you safe?

611
01:01:20,510 --> 01:01:22,730
 It's blood.

612
01:01:22,730 --> 01:01:24,220
 Hurry and come out if you don't want to die!

613
01:01:24,220 --> 01:01:25,220
 Help me, please!

614
01:01:25,220 --> 01:01:28,680
 It will be all over in seventy-two hours.
